 Job Description and Requirements 
 As Synopsys engages with clients in the application of our software security improvement methodologies, the Security Consultant joins in the execution and delivery of planned project deliverables and milestones that assist clients in learning, understanding, and applying Synopsys's secure software development methodologies. The Security Consultant typically has task responsibility within one project and develops the capability to perform tasks within one or more of Synopsys's security practices. The Security Consultant continuously learns and expands technical understanding. Security Consultants do some work from the office/home, but often go on site to help customers exterminate the bugs and untangle the flaws that make their systems insecure. Our Security Consultants make themselves and their team trusted advisors to our customers: they build the relationships that help create and identify follow-on assignments. 
Responsibilities: 
Source Code Analysis 
Software Penetration Testing 
Architecture Security Analysis 
Secure Software Design and Architecture 
Application Reverse Engineering 
Network Security Analysis 
Database Security Analysis 
Ideal Technical Skills: 
Familiarity with software security weakness, vulnerability, and secure code review 
Familiarity with software attack and exploitation techniques 
Familiarity with at least one software programming language and framework 
Experience with C/C++, .NET, Java, multiple OS and RDBMS 
Experience with other languages (e.g. JavaScript, Python, Ruby, PHP, Perl, COBOL, SQL, or Assembly) 
Experience conducting secure code review 
Experience conducting reverse engineering 
Experience performing web application penetration testing 
Qualifications: 
Proven written and verbal communication skills 
Awareness of end-to-end project management life-cycle including planning, execution and closeout 
Comfortable interfacing with clients and utilizing negotiation skills 
Ability to collaborate with project team members, take direction from the project lead and execute tasks consistently 
Bachelorâ€™s Degree in Computer Science, Engineering or equivalent. Masterâ€™s Degree preferred 
Willingness to travel 
